snippet.textDisplay:
Помню как то застрял на миссии, когда под землей в лаборатории надо было из палочек на экране создать одинаковую мелодию..

Не мог пройти год, забил..

Прошло лет 15.. Моя сонька давно не работала. Нашел малого, который продавал фатку. Купил у него.

Нарыл в гараже Резик 3. Протер, запустил..

Дошел до этой миссии и прошел ее за 2 минуты, наконец-то узнав, что же было дальше..

Миновало еще некоторое время.. И вот выходит ремастеринг. А мне сука 30, седина прявилась, да и пятки уже приходится шкрябать, но этот Резик обязательно пройду!

Лять, 3:20... Завтра на работу...

snippet.textDisplay:
—How will Capcom change the players' ability to run away from Nemesis compared to Mr. X?
—How about the overall encounters with Nemesis compare to Mr. X?
—How about the frequency in which Nemesis appears? I know Nemesis shows up sooner than Mr. X than later in the 1990s originals, but these are all great fascinations to wonder before the release.
I can see it, but there is only so much I can do with my imagination. Oh man, to be a developer and ponder these questions for months and months on end!
snippet.textOriginal:
—How will Capcom change the players' ability to run away from Nemesis compared to Mr. X? 
—How about the overall encounters with Nemesis compare to Mr. X? 
—How about the frequency in which Nemesis appears? I know Nemesis shows up sooner than Mr. X than later in the 1990s originals, but these are all great fascinations to wonder before the release.
I can see it, but there is only so much I can do with my imagination. Oh man, to be a developer and ponder these questions for months and months on end!

snippet.textDisplay:
Thanks Capcom! I know you must have made these recent REmakes back-to-back assuming RE:2 REmake would be a success. You were right, Capcom, and you even underestimated the remakes' selling power thanks to your fine judgement in RE:2's outstanding craftsmanship, which made it the top video game to own this year, full remake or new original game.


Content such as this is what will keep people coming back to RE, new and old-school fans. I am sure RE:3 will be outstanding too! Can't wait to stay up all night again upon RE:3 Remakes' release.
